==English==

===Etymology===
[[lighten|light(e)n]] + [[-ing]]

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈlaɪt.nɪŋ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"laIt.nIN/}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# The [[flash]] of [[light]] caused by the discharge of atmospheric [[electrical]] charge.
# The [[discharge]] of atmospheric [[electrical]] charge itself.
#: ''That tree was hit by '''lightning'''.''

====Usage notes====
* [[bolt]], [[flash]], [[strike]] are some of the words used to count lightning.

